### ZARA OKAFOR

**What she is:** A sorceress. New hire at Aeon Holdings, junior enchantment specialist. Walking catastrophe of uncontrolled magical vitality.

**What she isn't:** A chosen one. A rebel. A crusader. She's just a person who is powerfully, stubbornly, inconveniently *alive* in a place that has been engineered to suppress exactly that quality.

**Her magic:** Enormous raw power with almost no fine control. Zara doesn't cast spells so much as *happen* at the world magically. When she's happy, nearby plants grow. When she's angry, things crack. When she's genuinely delighted, people around her feel a warmth that has nothing to do with temperature. She's tried to learn control — years of training, tutors, exercises. It helps a little. But her power is tidal; you can build sea walls, but the ocean doesn't care about your architecture.

This is why she's in corporate work despite being, by raw metrics, extraordinarily powerful. No one will hire an uncontrolled sorceress for serious magical work. Too much liability. She took the Aeon job because it was *a* job, and she's been told her whole life to be grateful for whatever she can get.

**Her vitality:** Separate from her magic but related. Zara is simply, constitutionally *alive* in a way that most people aren't. She finds things interesting. She tastes her food. She asks people questions and listens to the answers. In a normal environment, she'd just be a warm, engaged person. In Aeon Holdings, she's a virus in the immune system of corporate undeath. She doesn't know she's doing anything unusual. She thinks everyone else is weird for *not* caring.

**Voice:** Direct, warm, curious, occasionally bewildered by the world around her. Not naive — she's seen enough to know things are broken — but fundamentally unwilling to accept that broken is the default setting.

**Sample voice:**
- *"I brought muffins. Actual muffins. From an oven. Why is everyone looking at me like I pulled a knife?"*
- *[to Milo] "You keep saying you don't care, but you're still here. Apathy has a much shorter commute."*
- *"They keep telling me I'm a 'culture fit risk.' I didn't know 'alive' was a culture."*
- *[on her magic] "I set a conference room fern on fire last Tuesday because the quarterly report made me angry. In my defense, it was a terrible report."*
- *[to Milo] "You built yourself a very elegant coffin, Milo. But you're still in it."*
- *"I don't understand how everyone just... accepts this. You go to work, you stop feeling things, you sign a form, and that's it? That's the plan?"*

